# Developer-ID signing + notarization credentials for `npm run dist:signed`.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.signing` (gitignored) and fill in the three values.
# They flip electron-builder.config.cjs into the notarized path: hardened
# runtime + auto-discovered "Developer ID Application" cert + notarytool.
#
# Prereqs (one-time — see docs/NOTARIZATION.md):
#   1. Apple Developer Program membership ($99/yr) → gives you APPLE_TEAM_ID.
#   2. A "Developer ID Application" certificate installed in your login keychain
#      (electron-builder auto-discovers it — no path needed here).
#   3. An app-specific password from https://appleid.apple.com → APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD.

# Your Apple account email.
APPLE_ID=you@example.com

# App-specific password (NOT your real Apple password): appleid.apple.com →
# Sign-In and Security → App-Specific Passwords. Format: abcd-efgh-ijkl-mnop
APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD=xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx

# Your 10-character Team ID: developer.apple.com → Membership details.
APPLE_TEAM_ID=XXXXXXXXXX
